abstract: A daughter seeks her father’s true voice to replace the memory of the sound of his death.
snippet: A daughter seeks her father’s true voice to replace the memory of the sound of his death.
lead_paragraph: FOR years I tried to construct a viable idea of my long-gone father by piecing together scraps of other people’s memories. I was only 6 when he died, and most of what I knew of him came from my mother, who considered him the embodiment of evil and tried at every opportunity to turn me against him. If I was going to be able to counter her poisonous tales, I needed empirical evidence of his humanity.
